---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '@/components/PortfolioHeader.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
import Terminal from '@/components/Terminal.astro';
import { site } from '@/data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Privacy and aggregate analytics policy for Mohit Sharma's portfolio."
>
  <Nav />
  <main id="main" class="section">
    <article class="container policy">
      <a class="back mono" href="/">← Portfolio</a>
      <p class="section-label">Privacy · Analytics</p>
      <h1>Measure the work, not the visitor.</h1>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          This is a static portfolio. It has no account system, advertising network,
          session replay, fingerprinting, or contact form database.
        </p>
        <h2>Aggregate analytics</h2>
        <p>
          When configured, this site sends bounded events to a collector owned by the
          site operator and hosted on Cloudflare Workers with aggregate storage in
          Cloudflare D1. There is no third-party analytics product or public dashboard.
          If the collector endpoint is not configured, no analytics request is made.
        </p>
        <p>The site limits custom measurement to these commands:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>contact and résumé actions;</li>
          <li>project live-site and source-code actions;</li>
          <li>work-detail and blog opens.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Event properties are limited to the current route, a stable content ID, and
          the command's placement. The collector may add coarse country and device class
          and stores only a referrer's hostname. Query strings, URL fragments, IP
          addresses, full user agents, email addresses, free-form text, résumé contents,
          cookies, persistent identifiers, and individual visitor records are not stored.
          Aggregate rows are deleted after 24 months.
        </p>
        <h2>Privacy signals</h2>
        <p>
          If your browser sends Global Privacy Control or Do Not Track, this site skips
          analytics initialization. Analytics is also disabled during local development
          and remains non-essential: blocking or losing the collector cannot change any
          page, command, download, or contact path.
        </p>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy can be sent to
          <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
  <Terminal />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main { background: var(--cp-bg-elevated); }
  .policy { max-width: 900px; }
  .back { display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 48px; color: var(--cp-accent); font-size: var(--type-label); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; }
  h1 { max-width: 14ch; margin-bottom: 56px; font-size: var(--type-feature); }
  .prose { margin-inline: auto; }
  @media (max-width: 620px) { h1 { font-size: 3.25rem; } }
</style>